The subsequent analysis encompasses four groups of procedures:

                           (1)

panel data preparation and structuring of variables, including analysis of collinearity;


                           (2)

selection of the basic model specification through the panel data modelling, including a precedent testing of variable stationarity;


                           (3)

formulation of the enhanced model specification with time lags and checking the marginal effects of variables;


                           (4)

implementation of geographic-specific effects to the model with the use of factorial analysis.

